1 (1) REQUIRE A RETAILER THAT CHARGES THE FEE TO PROVIDE A
2 RECEIPT TO A CUSTOMER THAT CLEARLY IDENTIFIES THE FEE AMOUNT CHARGED
3 AND NUMBER OF PLASTIC OR PAPER CARRYOUT BAGS ISSUED TO THE CUSTOMER;
4 AND
5 (2) PROVIDE FOR THE ENFORCEMENT OF ITEM (1) OF THIS
6 SUBSECTION THROUGH A SYSTEM OF CIVIL PENALTIES FOR VIOLATIONS AS
7 FOLLOWS:
8 (I) FOR A FIRST OFFENSE, A CIVIL PENALTY NOT EXCEEDING
9 $250;
10 (II) FOR A SECOND OFFENSE, A CIVIL PENALTY NOT EXCEEDING
11 $500; AND
12 (III) FOR A THIRD OR SUBSEQUENT OFFENSE, A CIVIL PENALTY
13 NOT EXCEEDING $1,000.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2025.

